Class ObjectFinder

java.lang.Object
ObjectFinder
public class ObjectFinder extends Object
The ObjectFinder class provides methods for finding objects such as Enquiry, Suggestion, Student, and Camp within their respective lists. It is used to locate objects based on various criteria, including unique identifiers and user roles.

    • findStudentRoleInCamp

      public String findStudentRoleInCamp(Student student, Camp camp)
      Determines the role of a Student in a specific Camp. Checks if the student is an attendee or a camp committee member.
      Parameters:
      student - The Student whose role is being determined.
      camp - The Camp in which the role is being checked.
      Returns:
      A String representing the role of the student in the camp. Possible return values: - "Attendee": If the student is part of the camp's list of attendees. - "Camp Committee Member": If the student is part of the camp's committee. - "None": If the student is not associated with the camp in any role.
